
[1]salvage

   SALV'AGE, n. [L. salvus, salvo.]

   In commerce, a reward or recompense allowed by law for the saving of a
   ship, or goods from loss at sea, either by shipwreck or other means, or
   by enemies or pirates.

                SALV'AGE, for savage, not used. [See Savage.]
